Alexander Rupsch wrote:
&gt;  &gt; Hi,all :
&gt;  &gt; I am a frech man of Junit, and I have a question.
&gt;  &gt; How can I test a case which I want it throws an exception.
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; How can I test the Exception is the one I expected.
&gt; 
&gt; public testException()
&gt; {
&gt;       try
&gt;       {
&gt;             exceptionThrowingStuff();
&gt;       } catch(Exception e)
&gt;       {
&gt;             assertTrue(e instanceof YourException);
&gt;             assertEquals(&quot;Your Message&quot;, e.getMessage());
&gt;       }
&gt;       assertTrue(&quot;No exeption has been thrown!&quot;, false);
&gt; }

assertTrue(message, false);

is equivalent to

fail(message);

Also, I would put fail() right after exceptionThrowingStuff().

Also, I would only catch YourException, and not Exception.

try {
     exceptionThrowingStuff();
     fail(&quot;Why didn&#39;t we throw an exception?&quot;);
}
catch (YourException expected) {
     assertEquals(&quot;Your message&quot;, expected.getMessage());
}
